clinical_history: Follow-up ultrasound for known liver lesion.
technique: Longitudinal, transverse, and oblique views obtained.
findings: Testes are coarse with normal vascularity.
Gallbladder shows homogeneous, no stones or wall thickening.

Uterus appears normal; endometrial thickness measures 6.0 mm.
Common bile duct measures 18.43 mm, within normal limits.
